Explanation of the demo (short):
- Buggy side: multiple asynchronous callbacks read the same sharedPercent, wait a bit, then write sharedPercent = prior + chunk. Because the reads happen at different times, some updates are lost, jumps occur, and the sum can exceed 100% (we deliberately don't clamp).
- Fixed side: tasks do not directly mutate shared state. Each contribution is applied inside runExclusive, which serializes updates so each updater sees an up-to-date value and the accumulator is clamped to 100%.

