  <div style="margin-top:16px;">
    <strong>Notes</strong>
    <ul class="small">
      <li>JavaScript runs on a single thread in the browser, but asynchronous callbacks interleave. If you do read-modify-write on shared mutable variables without coordination, callbacks can overwrite each other's updates.</li>
      <li>In the fixed version we avoid races by not having tasks read and then write a shared variable. Instead each task reports its contribution and the manager updates the aggregate.</li>
