Usage notes:
- Increase the number of tasks and the max delay to raise the chance of overlapping read-modify-write operations in the buggy version.
- The buggy panel lets each task read a shared variable, wait a little, then write back its increment. When two tasks overlap, one can overwrite the other's update or jointly push the value past 100%.
- The fixed panel has tasks report contributions to a central aggregator that sums them synchronously — this avoids the read-then-write race. Another fix (demonstrated in comments) is to serialize updates via a queue so only one task updates the shared variable at a time.

