Notes on the bug and the fix:
- The buggy code shows the classic lost-update race: Task A and Task B both read the same value X, compute X + a and X + b, then both write back; one write overwrites the other and its contribution is lost. If many increments are applied this way, you can skip percentages or temporarily see values >100 when contributions are large.
- The fix ensures only one place updates the shared total: tasks just report contributions; the updater applies them serially and caps at 100. This is equivalent to making the "read-modify-write" operation atomic or using a reducer/queue to serialize updates.

